{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Human Ro ribonucleoproteins (RNPs) are composed of one of the four small Y RNAs and at least two proteins, Ro60 and La. The La protein is a 47kDa polypeptide that frequently acts as an autoantigen in systemic lupus erythematosus and Sjogren's syndrome [[cite:PUB00014753]]. In the nucleus, La acts as a RNA polymerase III (RNAP III) transcription factor, while in the cytoplasm, La acts as a translation factor [[cite:PUB00014754]]. In the nucleus, La binds to the 3'UTR of nascent RNAP III transcripts to assist in folding and maturation [[cite:PUB00014760]]. In the cytoplasm, La recognises specific classes of mRNAs that contain a 5'-terminal oligopyrimidine (5'TOP) motif known to control protein synthesis [[cite:PUB00014755]]. The specific recognition is mediated by the N-terminal domain of La, which comprises a La motif and a RNA recognition motif (RRM). The La motif adopts an α/β fold that comprises a winged-helix motif [[cite:PUB00014761]].</p>\r\n<p>Homologous La domain-containing proteins have been identified in a wide range of organisms except Archaea, bacteria and viruses [[cite:PUB00003341]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "7soq", "name" "LaM domain of human LARP1 in complex with AAA RNA"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR22792" "LUPUS LA PROTEIN-RELATED"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "La domain containing protein", "short" "La_dom_prot"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 37, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 2668, "taxa" 9145, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 22147, "sets" 0, "proteins" 22147, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 13722}, "pathways" 3}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR045180", :literature {"PUB00003341" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Lin-Marq N" "Clarkson SG."], "ISO_journal" "J. Mol. 